President Trump gave remarks about his meeting with North Korean officials and the upcoming summit with Kim Jong Un. He stated that the meeting went well and that they will be meeting on June 12th in Singapore. Trump emphasized that the summit is a "get-to-know-you" situation and that it will be a process, not something that will be resolved in one meeting. He expressed optimism about the positive relationships being built and the potential for denuclearization. Trump also mentioned that he received a letter from Kim Jong Un and that they had a two-hour conversation during the meeting. He discussed the possibility of ending the Korean War and the involvement of other countries, such as South Korea, Japan, and China. Trump mentioned that economic aid may come from South Korea and China, and that he does not see the United States spending a lot of money. He also talked about the ongoing negotiations on trade deals, including NAFTA.